Step 4: Build and Execute (The "Accurate Way") 
1. Create the Bridge Network: 
docker network create sensor-net



2. Build the Images: 
docker build -f Dockerfile.logger -t data-logger . 
docker build -f Dockerfile.simulator -t sensor-sim .



3. Run Service A (Data Logger):
docker run -d \ 
 --name data-logger \ 
 --network sensor-net \ 
 -v $(pwd)/data:/data \ 
 data-logger



4. Run Service B (Sensor Simulator): 
docker run -d \ 
 --name sensor-sim \ 
 --network sensor-net \ 
 -e SERVICE_A_URL=http://data-logger:8000/log \ 
 sensor-sim



Step 5: Verify the Output 
Since we added PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1, the logs will no longer be blank. Check the Simulator's activity: 
docker logs -f sensor-sim



You should see: Sent temp 25.43C: Status 200  
Check the saved data on your Raspberry Pi: 
cat data/log.txt



You should see: Temperature: 25.43C: at [Date/Time] 
